<h1>Jamon Holmgren</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://jamonholmgren.com/now/">jamonholmgren.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Vancouver
WA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Founder and Chief Operating Officer at Infinite Red, <<a href="http://infinite.red/>,">http://infinite.red/>,</a> which is a mobile and web development shop in San Francisco and Portland.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I inspire trust in my team and my clients and get them to work together to make beautiful things.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I love people and great relationships as well as great software. I find the user experience fascinating, as well as beautiful code that nobody sees except the engineers.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
It's ordinary interactions that have an extraordinary impact on those around you. Make your mundane things (like saying "hello") be cheerful and positive.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
I'm going through a period of time where I'm not reading much nonfiction.  My workdays are taxing enough, so I'm keeping my down time to down time. I did really enjoy The Martian by Andy Weir recently.
</p>

